Dear Donut Dolly:<br><br>
I use the term with endearment.  You hit the nail on the head!  You did your job and I did mine.  I choose to believe that you did a very good job.  Furthermore, you don't need me to welcome you inside...you've earned the right.. but I will welcome you anyway.<br>
I also use the term REMF with endearment.. part of the time I was one.  By the way, there were some sorry people in the field... and some damn well dedicated ones in support roles.<br>
It is a tired subject to argue who's daddy can beat up who's daddy.  Can you imagine what it was like to work at the quartermaster morgue?<br>
My humor is often a little weird.  I make jest of many very honorable men on this site.. and they reciprocate.. maybe you can too at the risk of getting your butt kicked.. you card playing, Kool Aid pushing, Sugar breath Roundeye..<br>
I would throw my flak jacket in any mudhole to keep your malodorouse feet from getting wet.<br><br>
Mustang Two Four<br><br>
P.S.  Trade you a can of crumbled cookies and two VC flags for a carton of reconstituted milk and a can of Spam...<br>
P.S.S.  Matho Sapaween means Black Bear Woman... one who is good at looking inward. arJay eadHay, umbDay hitSay are secret, Special Forces code names that we use to identify Marines and Artillerymen respectively. 
